<WordWrap>Located just south of \c[4]Central Sector\c[0]'s very center, tourists may find this the perfect place to begin sightseeing.\fs[20]
• The \c[4]Castle\c[0] is home to \c[4]Elysia\c[0]'s government and nobles.
• The \c[4]Royal Library\c[0] houses the majority of knowledge for this world.
• And at \c[4]The Academy\c[0], one can become proficient with this world.
Choose a place to teleport to!
<WordWrap>Located at the north part of the \c[4]Central Sector\c[0], you will find the residence halls of many citizens.\fs[20]
• Just slightly northeast of this location is the \c[4]Santuary Inn\c[0], where any traveler can find a place to stay and rest.
• At the far northeast the \c[4]Grand Casino\c[0] welcomes gamblers.
• To the far northwest the \c[4]Gospel Church\c[0] helps revive the fallen.
Choose a place to teleport to!
<WordWrap>Located at the east part of the \c[4]Central Sector\c[0], travelers can find many things to do.\fs[20]
• At the \c[4]Guild Hall\c[0], you can find and recruit potential allies to assist you on your journey.
• The \c[4]Gensokyo Markplace\c[0] contains various goods for purchase.
• And should you be wounded, a trip to the \c[4]Elysian Hospital\c[0] will do your injuries good.
• At the far northeast the \c[4]Grand Casino\c[0] welcomes gamblers.
Choose a place to teleport to!
<WordWrap>Located at the west part of the \c[4]Central Sector\c[0], there exists many workshops and more!\fs[20]
• \c[4]T&B Financial\c[0] is there for all banking needs.
• Purchase a nice sword at \c[4]Halbarad's Weaponry\c[0].
• Find some nice armor at \c[4]Eric's Armory\c[0].
• \c[4]Munchin' Diner\c[0] is open all day for lunchin'!
• The \c[4]Gospel Church\c[0] helps revive the fallen.
Choose a place to teleport to!

<WordWrap>Central's Castle, located at the very heart of the \c[4]Central Sector\c[0]. This is heart of the \c[4]Elysian\c[0] government and where all the nobles live and work together to better the lives of its citizens.
Choose a place to teleport to!
<WordWrap>The \c[4]Royal Library\c[0] contains a wealth of knowledge regarding the world of \c[4]Elysia\c[0]. It is open for the public to help satiate anyone with a thirst for knowledge.
Choose a place to teleport to!

<WordWrap>\c[4]The Academy\c[0] is where young \c[4]Elysians\c[0] learn about the 24 classes \c[4]Elysia\c[0] has to offer. With thorough education, young \c[4]Elysians\c[0] are sure to become very capable.
Choose a place to teleport to!
<WordWrap>The \c[4]Grand Casino\c[0] welcomes those who wish to test their luck! Do you have the fortune to last in such a place?
Choose a place to teleport to!
<WordWrap>\c[4]Halbarad's Weaponry\c[0] is owned by the proud weaponsmith, \c[6]Halbarad\c[0]. Though a little eccentric, the quality of the weapons he can create is the real deal.
Choose a place to teleport to!

<WordWrap>\c[4]Eric's Armory\c[0] is ran by \c[6]Eric\c[0], former \c[4]Elysian\c[0] hero! Using his expertise, he creates armors for all adventurers to wear to keep them safe from the harm of battle.
Choose a place to teleport to!
<WordWrap>\c[6]Archeia\c[0] runs \c[4]Archeia's Accessories\c[0] as anyone could guess. She sells the most interesting and useful accessories found across her travels.
Choose a place to teleport to!
<WordWrap>Tourists, travelers, and even some citizens prefer to make their stay at the \c[4]Sanctuary Inn\c[0]. The low cost and well maintained lodging makes this inn extremely appealing to stay at.
Choose a place to teleport to!
<WordWrap>The \c[4]Gospel Church\c[0] is a place for those who have fallen through battle to revive at.
Choose a place to teleport to!
<WordWrap>The \c[4]Gensokyo Item Shop\c[0] is where you'll be able to buy potions, food, and other random items!
Choose a place to teleport to!
<WordWrap>The \c[4]Atelier Alchimiste\c[0] is home to \c[4]Elysia\c[0]'s greatest alchemy. Talented alchemists serve the public to synthesize new items!
Choose a place to teleport to!
